Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: US labour unions
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b043xnd7
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 3 Nov 1985
Labour unions lose power as disputes are settled by agreement rather than coercion. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014.